customers records available before a company representative picks 
up the call even though it makes some customers uneasy to be 
greeted by name before they identify themselves 
for the average phone user phone company officials say caller 
id simply lets them see whos trying to enter their residences by 
telephone 
you have the right to know when you answer the door to know 
whos there pitt says 
