campaign of violence in the last few years they have attacked 
sikhs who do not support their cause 
the radicals have rarely called strikes to highlight their 
cause relying mostly on individual killings at night and 
occaasional massacres 
the police blamed at least 1821 deaths in 1989 on the 
extremists in punjab where sikhs are in a slight majority 
nationwide they comprise 2 percent of the population sikhs 
