<TEXT>
bus fares and gasoline doubled and 
electricity quadrupled in price monday under a radical plan by the 
noncommunist government to transform polands centrally planned 
economy to capitalism 
poles fears of looming price increases were confirmed monday 
and finance minister leszek balcerowicz acknowledged hardships in 
