<TEXT>
new powers to outlaw religious 
discrimination in northern ireland came into force monday 
unemployment among the catholic minority in northern ireland is 
twice as high as for the protestant majority 
under the new laws a fair employment commission will 
investigate and monitor the actions of employers and force them to 
adopt fair employment practices 
employers must register the religious makeup of their workforce 
with the commission and where it is out of balance with the 
population in the area they will be ordered to take action to 
redress the imbalance 
where voluntary action towards equality fails the commission 
can back its orders with a variety of actions supervised by a fair 
employment tribunal 
anyone who is the victim of religious discrimination can be 
awarded up to 48000 employers who discriminate face sanctions 
that include being barred from government contracts grants or 
loans 
