workers in 10 states walked off their jobs in sympathy at one point 
pittstons coal subsidiary pittston coal group inc had said 
it could not afford to continue payments into the fund which 
covers 130000 pensioners who retired between 1947 and 1976 the 
company 560 of whose retirees are covered by the fund objected to 
making contributions to the pensions of thousands of employees of 
other companies 
the umw had said that other companies would attempt to escape 
from the fund if pittston were allowed to do so 
