prime minister mudar badran won a vote of 
confidence in the kingdoms revitalized parliament on monday after 
telling the lawmakers he will end jordans 22 years of martial law 
within six months 
badran also promised to repeal the 1953 law banning communism 
to reconsider the 1957 law banning political parties and to review 
the cases of political prisoners for a possible amnesty 
the government is committed to fulfilling the constitution in 
its spirit and its letter and intends to abolish martial law within 
a period of four to six months badran said in his twohour 
speech 
more 1000 people packed the public gallery and cheered as 
badran spoke and women wailed in joy in a traditiional arabic 
celebration afterward 
the vote followed more than two days of debate in the new 
80member parliament which is determined to pry further reforms 
from the cabinet badran was named prime minister dec 4 his 
cabinet was appointed two days later 
at king husseins insistence the november elections were the 
freest held here since the early days of independence in the 
mid1950s 
only nine deputies voted against the government on monday and 
six others abstained such a vote is required for all new cabinets 
badran had already removed most powers from military courts 
which have considered everything from homicides to political crimes 
to pricegouging on vegetables since martial law was declared 
during the 1967 war with israel 
in that conflict jordan lost the west bank which held half the 
seats in the old parliament husseins renunciation of sovereignty 
over the territory last year in favor of the palestine liberation 
organization paved the way for election of a revigorated and 
