the new government monday abolished 
the death penalty and the hated secret police as romanians 
celebrated their first noncommunist new years day in more than 
four decades 
interim president ion iliescu promised political pluralism and a 
shorter workweek reestablished private ownership of land and 
suspended wasteful construction projects in progress under toppled 
dictator nicolae ceausescu 
romanian radio reported no incidents of sniper fire or clashes 
between the army and diehard secret police loyal to ceausescu 
indicating a return to peace following two weeks of unrest that 
claimed thousands of lives 
people dressed in black lighted candles in central romana square 
